P. 339, side note. Blidworth is‘between Southwell and Mansfield, not far from Newstead Abbey, which is in the parish of Blidworth. The land between Blidworth and Rufford is still forest-land, and there is a regular crop of Robin Hood legends which have their centre at Blidworth. The hundreds of Broxtow, Thurgart0n‚ and Calverton, are all in the neighbourhood of Blidworth. Rayngwath, now Rainworth, is 1} miles east of Blidworth.
